it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.shorts

Class Short2LongAVLTreeMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.shorts.AbstractShort2LongFunction
      • it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.shorts.AbstractShort2LongMap
        • it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.shorts.AbstractShort2LongSortedMap
          • it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.shorts.Short2LongAVLTreeMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Function<java.lang.Short,java.lang.Long>, Short2LongFunction, Short2LongMap, Short2LongSortedMap, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<java.lang.Short,java.lang.Long>, java.util.SortedMap<java.lang.Short,java.lang.Long>

    public class Short2LongAVLTreeMap
extends AbstractShort2LongSortedMap
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    A type-specific AVL tree map with a fast, small-footprint implementation.

    The iterators provided by the views of this class are type-specific bidirectional iterators. Moreover, the iterator returned by iterator() can be safely cast to a type-specific list iterator.

        public long addTo(short k,

        Adds an increment to value currently associated with a key.

        Note that this method respects the default return value semantics: when called with a key that does not currently appears in the map, the key will be associated with the default return value plus the given increment.

        Parameters:

        incr - the increment.
        Returns:
        the old value, or the default return value if no value was present for the given key.
